-- Bernanke, G-8 Summit, Paris Air Show, NBA: Week Ahead June 15-22
-- B y   D i c k   S c h u m a c h e r ,   G r e g   M i l e s   a n d   J i m   M c D o n a l d
-- 2013-06-13T21:27:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-13/bernanke-g-8-summit-paris-air-show-nba-week-ahead-june-15-22.html
Federal Reserve Chairman  Ben S. Bernanke  and fellow policy makers may discuss when to begin
tapering the central bank’s $85 billion in monthly bond
purchases at their two-day meeting.  Group of Eight leaders will meet for their annual summit in
Northern Ireland with topics including tax evasion, trade,
Japanese economic stimulus and Syria’s civil war on the agenda.  Airbus SAS and Boeing Co. compete for wide-body jet orders
at the  Paris Air Show .  May housing data for both the U.S. and China will be
released. Votes will be counted in Iran’s presidential election.  Russian and international corporate leaders gather at the
St. Petersburg International Economic Forum.  SATURDAY, JUNE 15  To contact the reporters on this story:
